In a country where resistance is shifting from the town square to the battlefields, opposition leadership is becoming increasing masculinized as Islamists and armed groups play a larger role, marginalizing the voices of women. Nonetheless, Atassi and Zaitouneh continue to fight for democracy in Syria and for their right, as women, to take part in that fight.
